
[1]intendment

   INTEND'MENT, n. Intention; design; in law, the true meaning of a person
   or of a law, or of any legal instrument. In the construction of
   statutes or of contracts, the intendment of the same is, if possible,
   to be ascertained, that is, the true meaning or intention of the
   legislator or contracting party.
